5:
That was the last of the luggage we
needed to carry in, I believe.
8:
What shall we do now? We could
return to Starview, or we could stay
here a while longer.
13:
Well, since we're in a port like this, 
I figured we might as well get some
seafood!
20:
You're alive! Where have you been
all this time?
21:
You know what? Forget that—the
captain is waiting for you!
24:
Eduardo, who is this captain they're
talking about?
28:
That would be my direct superior—
a commissioned officer working for
the Gaean Navy.
34:
This is a military ship, right? Are you
sure it's okay for us to board as well?
36:
We have instructions to allow
Eduardo's companions in as well.
39:
Guess it really is all about who you
know. Wonder what kind of
reception we'll be getting.
43: I'd like to know that myself...
46:
I see. So you were stranded after
your research vessel was
destroyed...
47:
Then, these civilians from the Float
rescued you? Is that right?
53:
Well, it seems I've gotten all the
information I needed.
58:
Bring them all in for interrogation.
They may have come in contact
with highly confidential government
information.
61:
What, we don't get a say in any of
this?
66:
You saw nothing, understand? Go
back to the Float and await your
next assignment.
68:
What's with that glare? Show some
gratitude! Who do you think it was
that took care of you after your
family died in that accident?
73:
You're right. I do owe a debt to
you—and the Gaean government.
However...
76:
I'm afraid I can't comply with that
order.
83:
You know too much, Eduardo. All
that's left is for you to die.
90:
Eduardo died all those years ago in
that accident. You were living on
borrowed time. It's time to pay it
back.
98:
Why would a creature from the
depths come all the way to the
surface like this?!
102:
You idiot! Why the hell'd you save
him?!
106: I... can't abandon him like this.
109:
No matter his wrongdoings, he is still
the man who raised me.
112:
Did the kraken come in pursuit of
me?
114:
Is it seeking revenge for what
happened before?
118:
Alk, Nimbus! Create an opening for
me—it doesn't matter how short!
128:
I'm sorry to get you involved in all of
this.
Shall we return to Starview Village?
132: Are you sure you're content to do so?
135:
Yes. There's nothing left for me here
anymore.
137:
You heard the captain. The Eduardo
of this world died a long time ago.
141:
Uh-huh. Then who exactly is the guy
standing in front of us right now?
146:
I am merely... one Eduardo. A
different one. Nothing more, nothing
less.
148:
And it seems I've just regained my
freedom—which is to say I'm
unemployed. Would you be hiring,
by any chance?
149:
I would like to accompany you on
your journey. Will you have me?
155:
Of course we will.
Welcome aboard, Eduardo!
